  "medicalDecision": "Symptoms >10 days with purulent nasal discharge and maxillary sinus tenderness, worsening after initial improvement — consistent with acute bacterial sinusitis. No orbital or CNS warning signs. Amoxicillin-clavulanate prescribed with supportive nasal care and return precautions for vision change or severe headache.",
